cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper heavily relies on the theory of coded computation and its applications in edge computing. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper deals with distributed matrix-vector multiplication and offloading tasks to other devices for computation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper considers the heterogeneous and time-varying resources of edge devices and develops an adaptive algorithm for coded computation. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is relevant as the paper takes into account the privacy requirements of IoT applications and devices. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with communication costs and latency constraints in edge computing.
